<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Events in Gorazde -- 16 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Events in Gorazde -- 16 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Serbs Capture Strategic Peaks </H4>

<F P=102> AU1604142794 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1604142794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Obren Zerajic from Cajnice] </F>
  [Text] Fighting continues today in the area between Gorazde 
and Cajnice. The command of the Herzegovina Corps stresses that 
the units of the Srpska army are successfully carrying out their 
duties with the aim of enabling the expelled Serbian population 
from the right bank of the Drina River to return home and to 
save around 1,000 Serbs trapped in Gorazde itself. In fighting 
yesterday and overnight, the troops of the Herzegovina Corps 
have captured two important peaks -- Gradina and Jartiste, 
located some five kilometers east of Gorazde. These are the 
positions from which all Muslim attacks toward Cajnice were 
launched in the past 18 days. NATO planes are today again 
overflying the positions of the Serb troops between Gorazde and 
Cajnice. True, they are flying at an altitude over three 
kilometers, but an air raid alarm has been in effect in Cajnice 
since yesterday. The local population is observing the alarm. 
There have been no losses in the ranks of the Herzegovina Corps 
in the past 24 hours. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

