<H3> <TI>   Events in Gorazde -- 16 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Events in Gorazde -- 16 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Churkin: No Serb Plan To Take Gorazde </H4>

<F P=102> AU1604142894 Paris AFP in English 1412 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1604142894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, April 16 (AFP) -- Russian special envoy on 
ex- Yugoslavia, Vitaliy Churkin, said Saturday [16 April] 
Bosnian Serb forces had assured him that they did not plan to 
take the besieged Moslem enclave of Gorazde. 
  Speaking here after meeting UN special envoy on 
ex-Yugoslavia 
Yasushi Akashi, Churkin said: "The two very firm assurances I 
think I got from them (the Bosnian Serbs) is that it is not 
their intention to take the town. It is not their intention to 
shell the town." 
  Serb forces were Saturday consolidating their position 
around 
the eastern town, which now shelters around 70,000 people, after 
capturing the last strategic positions in the area Friday. 

</TEXT>

