<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Events in Gorazde -- 16 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Pilot Ejected to Safety </H4>

<F P=102> AU1604172594 Paris AFP in English 1715 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1604172594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brussels, April 16 (AFP) -- The pilot of the Sea 
Harrier jump jet shot down over Gorazde in Bosnia-Hercegovina 
ejected from the airplane and escaped with only "minor 
scratches," a NATO spokesman said here Saturday. 
  He said the aircraft had been on a non-offensive operation 
over the mainly-Moslem UN-protected "safe area," currently under 
Serb attack, when it was shot down. 

</TEXT>

