<H4>    UN Calls for NATO Air Strikes </H4>

<F P=102> AU1604164894 Paris AFP in English 1637 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1604164894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brussels, April 16 (AFP) -- The United Nations 
called for NATO air strikes over the UN-declared "safe haven" of 
Gorazde, a spokesman said here Saturday [16 April], shortly 
after the downing of a NATO jet over the eastern Bosnian Moslem 
enclave. 
  The NATO spokesman said the downed Harrier jump-jet, from 
which the pilot reportedly ejected, was shot down during a 
"non-offensive" operation over the enclave. 

</TEXT>

