<H4>    UNPROFOR Threatens Air Strikes </H4>

<F P=102> AU1604193694 Paris AFP in English 1922 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1604193694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, April 16 (AFP) -- The UN Protection Force 
Saturday gave an ultimatum to Bosnian Serbs besieging the Moslem 
enclave of Gorazde, threatening air strikes if they advance 
further on the town, a spokesman said. 
  Major Rob Annink said UN special envoy Yasushi Akashi had 
called for NATO air support earlier in the day, and said this 
could be activated at any moment. "Do not shoot at the town, do 
not advance," the text of the ultimatum read, according to 
Annink. 

