  [Text] Sarajevo, April 17 (AFP) -- NATO warplanes flew low 
over Gorazde on Sunday [17 April], a UN Protection Force 
spokesman said here, as Bosnian Serb tanks entered the 
UN-declared "safe-haven" sowing panic among the civilian 
population. 
  Lt. Colonel Richard Pernod said aircraft of the North 
Atlantic Treaty Organisation were conducting close air support 
operations over the enclave. 

</TEXT>

