<H3> <TI>   Events in Gorazde -- 17 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Events in Gorazde -- 17 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    `Horror, Hell' as Tanks Enter Gorazde </H4>

<F P=102> LD1704162994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1600 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1704162994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] It is still not known how long Gorazde will live. 
Is it a question of minutes or hours. It is certainly not a 
question of days, as chetnik tank have already entered the town. 
The chaos has begun; horror and hell are in every place [words 
indistinct]. Chetniks are shooting at the people with snipers 
and anti-aircraft weapons. There are many casualties but their 
number is not known in this chaos. Unarmed people are facing 
chetnik tanks. NATO planes are agonizing [words indistinct]. 
The town center of Gorazde has become a real enclosure for 
children, women, and the elderly waiting for the death they have 
already seen. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-8754 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu074_i_94027" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-074 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  17 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Events in Gorazde -- 17 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Events in Gorazde -- 17 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    UN Spokesman on Casualties </H4>

<F P=102> LD1704192494 Lisbon RDP Antena 1 Radio Network in Portuguese 
1700 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1704192494 </F>
<F P=104>  Lisbon RDP Antena 1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] [Announcer] The Bosnian Serb leader promised an 
immediate cease-fire in Gorazde following a long meeting with 
the UN'S special envoy. [passage omitted] RDP-1 has learned 
that the city is under heavy fire, tens of thousands of people 
fleeing. There have been more than 1,200 casualties since the 
beginning of the Serb offensive. The Serbs have entered Gorazde 
with combat vehicles, as UN spokesman Manuel Almeida told us. 
  [Begin recording] [Almeida] We were informed by our 
colleagues in Gorazde that the local people had told them that 
the Serbs were entering the city with tanks. [passage omitted] 
We did not see this because we are in shelters as the city is 
being bombarded. Our colleagues are in protected shelters and 
the local people went to see them and tell them. Also, what we 
can see is that the population is in a great panic. This is 
understandable since we estimate that during the offensive of 
the last few days, last two weeks, about 25,000 people have been 
moved within the Gorazde enclave; the great majority seeking 
refuge in the city of Gorazde or in its outskirts. The city 
does not have the conditions to receive so many people, many 
buildings have been destroyed. 
  [Announcer] How many casualties are there? 
  [Almeida] There are about 1,200 people dead or injured. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

