<H4>    Attack Continues Despite Cease-Fire </H4>

<F P=102> AU1704183894 Paris AFP in English 1827 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1704183894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, April 17 (AFP) -- Serb tanks were 
continuing to fire on the Moslem town of Gorazde, a UN "safe 
haven," a ham operator said Sunday, despite the declaration 
earlier of an immediate ceasefire there by Bosnian Serb leader 
Radovan Karadzic. 
  Shells from Serb tanks, which rolled into the town Sunday 
afternoon, were still raining down on the town said the radio 
operator who contacted Sarajevo around 7:45 p.m. (1745 GMT). 

</TEXT>

