<H3> <TI>   Events in Gorazde -- 18 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Events in Gorazde -- 18 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Serbs Say Muslims Firing on Serb Lines </H4>

<F P=102> LD1804090294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0757 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1804090294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Cajnice, 18 Apr (TANJUG) -- The command of the 
Herzegovina Corps [of the Srpska army] announced this morning 
that, following yesterday's cease-fire on the Gorazde 
battlefield, Serb forces stopped advancing toward Gorazde. 
  However, following a brief lull overnight, the Muslims in 
Gorazde started opening sniper and antiaircraft fire on the Serb 
lines, and the fire is being stepped up. 
  The command of the Serb forces issued sharp warnings that if 
the fire does not stop immediately it will respond with all 
available weapons. [passage omitted] 
  After they captured Biserna hill above Gorazde yesterday, 
the 
Herzegovina Corps' fighters liberated the whole of the right 
bank of the River Drina. The last Muslim soldiers fled 
yesterday afternoon across bridges in Gorazde to the left bank. 
  The Serb forces' frontline is currently in the town itself, 
on the right bank of the River Drina. Serb units yesterday 
advanced considerably from the direction of Kopaci, north of 
Gorazde, and reached the town's suburbs. 
  A considerable chunk of territory on the left bank of the 
Drina was also liberated yesterday. The areas of Jelah, 
Konjbaba, and Sjedokosa are now under Serb control. 
  In addition to the central town area, the Muslims control 
the 
area on the left bank of the River Drina, 7 or 8 kms toward Foca. 

</TEXT>

