<H3> <TI>   Events in Gorazde -- 18 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Events in Gorazde -- 18 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Officials Appeal to Citizens To Resist </H4>

<F P=102> AU1804111194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1804111194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] As a result of the extremely difficult and dramatic 
situation in Gorazde, the residents of this town were addressed 
by Rijad Rastic, president of the Gorazde District, and Esad 
Ohranovic, president of the Executive Council. 
  [Begin Rastic recording] I, Rijad Rasic, president of the 
Gorazde District, appeal to all those who live in Gorazde not to 
cause panic through their behavior, that all those capable of 
fighting to report to their nearest unit, to put old people, 
women and children in safe places to avoid shells, and to avoid 
unnecessary walking around. 
  Check all the information that your receive in several 
places. Do not listen to panic and those who do not think well 
of our people. You finally know [words indistinct] let down. 
The courageous defenders are successfully doing everything to 
save the people from the chetniks. Help our defenders as much 
as you can. God is protecting Gorazde. [end recording] 
  [Begin Ohranovic recording] There is only death in Gorazde. 
There is no one to stop this death and horror. Fighting is 
taking place around the hospital itself. In the past hour, 
hundreds of shells have landed on the town. The hospital, the 
International Red Cross, and collective accommodation are all 
being targeted. We demand once again that a stop be put to 
this. I do not know whether I will have the opportunity to 
repeat this appeal. 
  I appeal to the defenders of Gorazde and the residents of 
Gorazde to devote everything to the service of defense. Do not 
fall for rumors and disinformation. The town must be defended. 
Do not forget the dead and wounded. Do not forget your 
co-fighters without arms and legs. It is better to die than be 
taken into the hands of the enemy alive. Do everything possible 
to prevent the enemy from entering the town and carrying out an 
unprecedented slaughter. I know that we can and want do it. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

