<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Events in Gorazde -- 18 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Events in Gorazde -- 18 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    UN Evacuates Remaining Soldiers </H4>

<F P=102> AU1804113494 Paris AFP in English 1111 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1804113494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Zagreb, April 18 (AFP) -- The United Nations pulled 
the last of its soldiers out of the Moslem enclave of Gorazde 
overnight Sunday to Monday [17-18 April], a French military 
source said Monday. 
  Five UN observers were evacuated by helicopter along with 
seven forward ground controllers, used to direct NATO warplanes 
to their ground targets. 

</TEXT>

