<H3> <TI>   Events in Gorazde -- 18 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Events in Gorazde -- 18 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Hospital, Red Cross Hit </H4>

<F P=102> AU1804082194 Paris AFP in English 0810 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1804082194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Geneva, April 18 (AFP) -- Bosnian Serbs resumed 
intensive shelling Monday [18 April] on the Moslem enclave of 
Gorazde in eastern Bosnia, hitting the hospital roof and Red 
Cross centre, a UN spokeswoman said here. 
  "The night was quiet, but gunfire started again this 
morning," said Sylvana Foa, spokeswoman for the UN High 
Commissioner for Refugees. A shell was falling every 20 
seconds, she said. 
  "The hospital was hit on the roof," she said, adding that 
the 
International Committee of the Red Cross centre in the town was 
also hit. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

