<H3> <TI>   Events in Gorazde -- 18 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Events in Gorazde -- 18 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Karadzic: Serb Forces To Withdraw </H4>

<F P=102> LD1804144094 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1418 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1804144094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, 18 Apr (TANJUG) -- The office of president 
of the Srpska republic, Radovan Karadzic, stated today that -- 
following yesterday's meeting with UN Secretary General 
Butrus-Ghali's special envoy Yasushi Akashi and his appeal -- 
the authorities of the Srpska republic have decided, as a sign 
of good will, to immediately carry out or help in carrying out 
the following: 
  1. Serb forces will remain outside a three-kilometer 
exclusion zone, on the left bank of the Drina River near 
Gorazde, and will agree to the immediate deployment of UNPROFOR 
[UN Protection Forces] troops. 
  2. Medical aid and the evacuation of the wounded and sick 
from Gorazde and other locations. 
  3. UN High Commissioner for Refugees, International 
Committee of the Red Cross and Handicap International may 
continue their humanitarian convoys. 
  4. Freedom of movement for all humanitarian workers on the 
entire territory of the Srpska republic. 
  5. Police units of the Srpska republic will escort all 
convoys, it is said in the statement released by the office of 
the president of the Srpska republic. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

