<H3> <TI>   Events in Gorazde -- 18 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Events in Gorazde -- 18 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Promises To Withdraw Artillery </H4>

<F P=102> AU1804151994 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1455 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1804151994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Mirjana Kuzma report] </F>
  [Text] This afternoon, president of the Srpska republic 
Radovan Karadzic met suddenly and unexpectedly with the chief of 
the UN Protection Forces [UNPROFOR] Civilian Sector (Viktor 
Andreeyev) in Pale. 
  During the meeting, Karadzic and (Andreeyev) tried to 
harmonize the agreement reached yesterday at the meeting of the 
Srpska republic political leadership with UN special envoy to 
the former Yugoslavia Yasushi Akashi. The organs of the Srpska 
republic promised to realize the agreement on the withdrawal of 
the Serbian artillery from the 3 km zone in the sector of 
Gorazde on the left bank of the Drina River where UNPROFOR 
forces will subsequently be deployed. 
  The political and military leadership of the Srpska republic 
will assist in the evacuation of all injured and sick from 
Gorazde and other settlements, while convoys of all 
international humanitarian organizations will be guaranteed a 
safe passage thought the Serbian territories in the company of 
the Srpska republic police. 

</TEXT>

