<H4>    Serbs Agree To `Immediate' Cease-Fire </H4>

<F P=102> AU1804153094 Paris AFP in English 1521 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1804153094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, April 18 (AFP) -- Bosnian Serb 
authorities have agreed to an "immediate" ceasefire at Gorazde, 
an UNPROFOR [United Nations Protection Force] spokesman said 
here Monday. 
  The ceasefire was due to come into effect early Monday 
afternoon, said UN Protection Force spokesman Eric Chaperon. 

</TEXT>

