<H3> <TI>   Events in Sarajevo -- 17 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Events in Sarajevo -- 17 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    British Soldier Killed at Checkpoint </H4>

<F P=102> LD1704122094 London PRESS ASSOCIATION in English 1157 GMT 17 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1704122094 </F>
<F P=104>  London PRESS ASSOCIATION </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Gavin Cordon] </F>
  [Excerpt] An off-duty British soldier serving with the 
United Nations has been shot dead in Sarajevo, the UN said today. 
  A spokesman for the UN Protection Force [UNPROFOR] in the 
Bosnian capital told Reuters the man, who was believed to be in 
civilian clothing, was killed at a checkpoint manned by the 
mainly Muslim Bosnian government army. 
  The incident, which happened early today, is being 
investigated by UNPROFOR and the Bosnian military police. A 
Ministry of Defence spokesman said they were seeking further 
details. 
  According to a BBC report, Bosnian forces manning the 
checkpoint opened fire after the soldier failed to stop. He 
reportedly started to run and was hit in the head. 
  He is the fourth British soldier to die while serving with 
the UN in Bosnia. A British Sea Harrier pilot ejected safely 
after Serb forces shot down the helicopter over the besieged 
town of Gorazde yesterday, and a British SAS man acting as a 
forward observer in the town for UN aircraft was killed and a 
second injured on Friday. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

