<H3> <TI>   Events in Sarajevo -- 17 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Events in Sarajevo -- 17 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Muslims Capture Summit, TV Relay </H4>

<F P=102> LD1704195794 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1914 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1704195794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 17 Apr (TANJUG) -- Muslim units carried 
out a military operation today, capturing the summit of Mount 
Bjelasnica and the TV relay facility on the summit, the 
information service of the Srpska republic army's main 
headquarters said this evening. 
  ``As we have already informed the public, UN Protection 
Forces [UNPROFOR] units which were deployed on Mount Igman and 
Mount Bjelasnica have been withdrawing to Hrasnica and Sarajevo 
airport over the last few days, thus violating the cease-fire 
agreement and leaving the area they controlled to Muslim forces, 
the statement says. It adds that some UNPROFOR troops stayed on 
to control certain positions, including the summit of Mount 
Bjelasnica and its TV relay facility. 
  "However, the Muslim forces today carried out a military 
operation and captured the summit of Mount Bjelasnica and the TV 
relay," the statement of the main headquarters of the Srpska 
republic army says. Thus, the area handed over by the Srpska 
republic army to UNPROFOR under the terms of the cease-fire 
agreement has been seized by members of the so-called 
Bosnia-Herzegovina army. This creates conditions for offensive 
operations toward Trnovo and Rogoj, as well as major offensive 
operations to split and capture the Serb-held parts of Sarajevo. 
It is certain that the Muslims and UNPROFOR have used deceit to 
violate the terms of the peace agreement. 
  "Nothing can be said with certainty about the fate of 
UNPROFOR members who stayed on at the summit of Mount Bjelasnica 
until the violent act committed by the Muslims," the statement 
issued by the information service of the main headquarters of 
the Srpska republic army says in conclusion. 

</TEXT>

