<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Soldiers from the 1st Corps of the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Army carried out a successful military 
operation today by liberating the Nisici plateau, north of 
Sarajevo, and a part of the occupied territory between Sarajevo 
and Olovo. Velid Djindo reporting from Olovo. 
  [Djindo] The aggressor's plan, named Zvijezda 94, was 
thwarted by a well-planned and coordinated operation by units 
from the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army's 1st Corps. More important 
positions have been liberated in a brilliant counterattack and a 
10-kilometer-wide part of the front line was pushed between 1 
and 5 kilometers forward. 
  Our units have captured the villages of Milovac, Dovorine, 
Orahak, Karacici, Dalja, Brda, Zicki, and Citlucki Zalik as well 
as the Bukva, Kosijenci, Mali Hum, and Veliki Hum hills. New 
areas are being captured. Our soldiers have seized large 
quantities of weapons, ammunition, and military equipment and 
the enemy suffered considerable losses in manpower. [passage 
omitted] 

