<H3> <TI>   Events in Sarajevo -- 17 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Events in Sarajevo -- 17 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Muslim Troops Leave Sarajevo for Gorazde </H4>

<F P=102> LD1704132294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1227 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1704132294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Zvornik, Bratunac, 17 Apr (TANJUG) -- Muslim 
military engineers have continued work in the Sarajevo area, 
especially in Sokolje and Mojmilo, in order to get close to the 
Serb defense lines, Srpska republic army [VRS] sources have told 
a TANJUG correspondent. 
  Serb military sources are saying that the pull-out of Muslim 
units and military equipment from Sarajevo has continued via a 
tunnel underneath Sarajevo airport and on board lorries across 
the runway, before the very eyes of UN peacekeepers. 
  The Serb military sources are also saying that, once out of 
Sarajevo, Muslim units are setting off in the direction of 
Hrasnica and Mount Igman in an attempt to link up in force with 
the area around Gorazde. The VRS are foiling all these 
attempts, while Muslim soldiers, who surrendered to the Serb 
side upon leaving Sarajevo, are talking about an "extremely low 
morale among Muslim formations" which are heading toward 
Gorazde, because "a vast majority do not want to take part in 
these senseless actions," the VRS sources explain. 

</TEXT>

