<H3> <TI>   UN Troops Accused of Joining Muslims in Attack </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Troops Accused of Joining Muslims in Attack </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1704123194 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1207 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1704123194 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, 17 Apr (TANJUG) -- In the northeast 
section of the Sarajevo theater of war this morning, Muslim 
forces attacked Serb positions near the Pretis industrial site 
in Vogosca and the suburbs of Brioni and Ugljesic, Serb military 
sources report. 
  According to the same sources, some 50 antitank shells were 
fired and dozens of hand grenades were hurled. 
  The conflict culminated when UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] 
troops, stationed at Glavica and Sabanove Kuce, joined the 
Muslim forces, the Serb military forces claim. They say that 
the UNPROFOR and government troops were targeting the Serb 
positions with antiaircraft guns and incendiary ammunition. A 
trench in the central section of the Serb positions in Ugljesic 
was destroyed. 
  The Serb fighters returned fire in retaliation for these 
joint operations, so a lull followed 20 minutes later. 
  The Serbian military forces also report that there were no 
dead or wounded on the Serb side and that the front lines remain 
unchanged. 

</TEXT>

