1500 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1604160594 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Three persons have been killed and 10 injured in 
Serb attacks on Brcko. Over 3,000 shells have landed on the 
defense positions of the Brcko municipality, the political 
department of the 108th Croat Defense Council [HVO] Infantry 
Brigade has reported. The Serbs have been using howitzers, 
tanks, multiple rocket-launchers, and mortars, while a number of 
commando groups have attempted to break through. These attempts 
have been successfully foiled. 
  An HVO advance party has reported that the Serb formations 
are again concentrating in several locations, while intelligence 
officers have said that a group of the so-called Bijeljina 
Panthers, a criminal formation that has taken part in some dozen 
massacres in northeast Bosnia, has arrived in Brcko. 

</TEXT>

