<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest (DDP/ADN)--Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel 
met his Hungarian counterpart Geza Jeszenszky in Budapest today. 
The main focus of the meeting was Hungary's integration into 
the European Union (EU), the Western European Union (WEU), and 
NATO. 
  Kinkel will address a joint forum this evening of the 
Friedrich Naumann Foundation and the opposition Federation of 
Young Democrats (Fidesz) and the Alliance of Free Democrats 
(SZDSZ) on the subject of "The Visegrad Countries and the EU". 
  [Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian at 1700 GMT on 
15 April reports that Foreign Minister Jeszenszky spoke to 
journalists after his discussions with Kinkel and denied that 
Hungary and Ukraine support the Greek-Romanian-Bulgarian 
proposal for lifting the embargo against rump Yugoslavia.] 

</TEXT>

