<F P=101> Federal </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lilic Chairs Supreme Defense Council Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lilic Chairs Supreme Defense Council Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1504145894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1317 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1504145894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 15 Apr (TANJUG) -- A session of the 
Supreme Defense Council presided over by FRY President Zoran 
Lilic was held in Belgrade today. 
  As the Yugoslav president's military office has announced, 
in 
addition to the members of the Supreme Defense Council, Serbian 
President Slobodan Milosevic, and Montenegrin President Momir 
Bulatovic, the session was also attended by FRY Prime Minister 
Rade Kontic, FRY Defense Minister Pavle Bulatovic, and Colonel 
General Momcilo Perisic, chief of the General Staff of the 
Yugoslav Army. 
  The Supreme Defense Council examined the overall military 
and 
political situation in the region and the level of combat 
readiness of the Yugoslav Army and said that the council's 
decisions have been successfully implemented. 
  Other issues of importance for the defense and security of 
the country were also discussed at the session today. 

</TEXT>

