<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Weapons Under UN Control `Stolen' by Serbs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Weapons Under UN Control `Stolen' by Serbs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1704204594 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
2000 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1704204594 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Serb forces in Baranja, in east Croatia, have taken 
part of the heavy weapons which were under the control of the UN 
Protection Force, according to Belgian military spokesman 
Colonel (Fredi Van Weg). 
  A group of 520 Belgian soldiers is deployed in Baranja, 
which 
has been under Serb occupation for two years. In early April, 
Croatia agreed on a cease-fire with the rebel Serbs and, under 
the agreement, the Serbs placed their heavy weapons under UN 
control in six warehouses. 
  The fact that a certain number of weapons have been stolen 
should be condemned, because this will have a negative impact on 
the peace process which has taken off well, Colonel (Van Weg) 
said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

