<H3> <TI>   Events in Gorazde -- 15 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Events in Gorazde -- 15 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    `Massive Exodus' of Muslims </H4>

<F P=102> AU1504175794 Paris AFP in English 1744 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1504175794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Zagreb, April 15 (AFP) -- Bosnian Moslems started a 
massive exodus from outlying districts in the Serb-besieged 
Moslem enclave of Gorazde on Friday [15 April] to seek shelter 
within the town, UNHCR spokesman Peter Kessler said. 
  "The situation is extremely tense" said Kessler, adding that 
he expected the situation in the eastern enclave to deteriorate. 
  The exodus from northern and northeastern districts started 
around 3:30 P.M. (1330 GMT) and was still going on at 7 P.M., 
Kessler added. 

</TEXT>

