<H3> <TI>   Events in Gorazde -- 16 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Events in Gorazde -- 16 April </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Izetbegovic Asks Clinton for Help </H4>

<F P=102> LD1604224794 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2200 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1604224794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Alija Izetbegovic, president of the presidency of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, has sent a letter to U.S. President Bill 
Clinton in which he asks him to find a way of helping the 
population of Gorazde. 
  The lives of many people and also the reputation of the 
United States are at stake. If force and deceit triumph, this 
will not only be a defeat for Bosnia, but also for many 
important institutions in which we have acted together. We must 
prevent this defeat, the letter from President Izetbegovic says. 
  President Izetbegovic sent this letter to the heads of state 
or government of Russia, France, Great Britain, Germany, Turkey, 
and Saudi Arabia. 

</TEXT>

