  [Text] Viktor Mikhaylov and Andriy Vasylyshyn, interior 
ministers of Bulgaria and Ukraine, signed a cooperation 
agreement today. The agreement provides for joint action in 
combating organized crime, narcotics trafficking, and illegal 
trade in strategic raw materials, as well as the exchange of 
information on persons being sought and other similar problems. 
The two delegations were received by Deputy Prime Minister 
Evgeni Matinchev. 

