<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official: Nation May Join NATO in 2 Years </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official: Nation May Join NATO in 2 Years </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1504154594 Prague CESKY DENIK in Czech 13 Apr 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU1504154594 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CESKY DENIK </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "jiz": "The Entry of the Czech Republic Into </F>
the North Atlantic Alliance May Be Feasible in Two Years"] 
  [Text] Prague--A feasible time for us to join NATO would 
be after 1996, when the first stage of the transformation of our 
Army is completed. This is what Vladimir Suman, chairman of the 
Defense and Security Committee, told the CESKY DENIK 
correspondent after meeting [NATO representatives] Loic Bouvard 
and Peter Corterier. Furthermore, according to him, it is in 
NATO's interest that a country with our strategic location and 
economic stability become a member. Suman said that the NATO 
representatives' assessment of our republic was unequivocally 
favorable. Only Partnership for Peace will test our specific 
military ability to cooperate with the NATO armies and the 
possibility of joining this structure. In his opinion, the 
security development in Europe may electrify the situation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

