<F P=106> [Article by "(jis)": "The Establishment of a New Party"] </F>
  [Text] Kolin--At its extraordinary nationwide assembly, 
the Movement of Retired People for Social Security decided to 
transform itself into a political party--Pensioners for Social 
Securities. This change will not reportedly have any impact on 
the political line and the party's decision to fight on behalf 
of socially endangered individuals among our people. The main 
stress will be laid on the existential interests of the 
pensioners. According to Otakar Skalsky, press spokesman of the 
party, thousands of new members have joined the party recently. 

