<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   More UN Military Observers Detained </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More UN Military Observers Detained </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1904072094 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 0600 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1904072094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Serbian forces have detained two more UN military 
observers from Indonesia serving in Sarajevo. This brings to six 
the total number of Indonesian military observers detained by 
the Serbs. 
  A press release issued by the Indonesian Armed Forces 
headquarters in Jakarta said the six Indonesian observers are 
Major (Didi Sumardi), Major (Muhiddin), Major (Toto Sudarto), 
Major (Dwi Istianto), Major (B. Irawan), and Captain (Suryawan). 
They are in good condition but are not allowed to leave their 
post. 
  In addition to the Indonesian officers, UN observers from 
Bangladesh, the Netherlands, and Jordan have also been detained 
by the Serbs. Efforts to free them are now being made by the 
UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] commander and UN officials by 
holding talks with the Serbian and Russian officials. 

</TEXT>

