<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gorazde Situation Worsens as Attack Continues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gorazde Situation Worsens as Attack Continues </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Serbs Begin Fresh Attack </H4>

<F P=102> LD1904072694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0600 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1904072694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to the latest report from Gorazde, 
following last night's relative lull, this morning at about 0400 
Karadzic's Serbs launched fresh attacks on this town. Here is a 
report from Gorazde. 
  [Correspondent Fahrudin Brkic] [passage indistinct] in the 
southeast part did not stop for a single moment. There was no 
respite either in an unprecedented exodus of people from their 
burning villages. [placenames indistinct] villages were put to 
the torch by the chetniks yesterday. The aggressor's infantry 
attacks were accompanied by artillery that pounded the entire 
town and its outlying suburbs until 0200 this morning. 
  Following a brief lull, these operations resumed at about 
0400. On the 20th day of the offensive against Gorazde [word 
indistinct] of this town has reached its culmination. Fahrudin 
Brkic reporting for Bosnia-Herzegovina Radio. 

</TEXT>

