<H4>    Muslims Firing From `Fortresses' </H4>

<F P=102> LD1904084294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0809 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1904084294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Cajnice, 19 Apr (TANJUG) -- Srpska republic army 
positions on the right bank of the Drina River have been under 
fierce Muslim fire from Gorazde since yesterday, despite the 
cease-fire agreement signed by Radovan Karadzic and Yasushi 
Akashi two days ago, the command of the Herzegovina Corps 
reports. [passage omitted] 
  Serb military sources point out that all residential 
buildings in Gorazde, including the buildings of international 
humanitarian organizations, are in fact fortresses from which 
fire is being directed toward Serb positions. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

