<H3> <TI>   Gorazde Situation Worsens as Attack Continues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gorazde Situation Worsens as Attack Continues </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Siladzic: Bosnia `Betrayed' by UN </H4>

<F P=102> TA1804155194 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1510 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1804155194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, Bosnia-Herzegovina April 18 (A.A.) -- 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Prime Minister Haris Silajdzic on Monday said 
that his country has been betrayed by the United Nations, adding 
there is nothing to be done "as they (United Nations) do not 
want to do anything. The West is afraid of Russia." 
  Silajdzic said the problem lies in the fear of the West of 
Russia which wants a "greater fascist Serbia." 
  He said NATO can do whatever the United Nations wants, but 
the United Nations is not doing anything. 
  "It is a vicious circle," Silajdzic said. "A scenario to 
kill 
Gorazde and give it to the Serbs." 
  Silajdzic said Bosnia is alone against the world, but 
expressed belief Turkey is doing its best, adding he is 
constantly in contact with President Suleyman Demirel and 
Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin. 
  On the latest developments in Gorazde, he said he contacted 
the town half an hour ago and that the West has shown the green 
light to kill the city and its inhabitants. 
  "It is proof that the West will not do anything to help and 
will not lift the arms embargo," he said. 
  He said according to latest information from Gorazde, Serbs 
are burning everything in the town and there is a massacre going 
on. 
  Silajdzic also said that the Serbs want to take the 
defenseless city after forcing UN observers and any other UN 
officials out of Gorazde. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

