<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Srpska Army Repulses Muslim Attack on Brcko </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Srpska Army Repulses Muslim Attack on Brcko </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1804192294 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1914 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1804192294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Banja Luka, April 18 (TANJUG) -- The army of the 
Bosnian Serb republic on Monday repulsed a strong combined 
Moslem attack on Brcko in the north of the former Yugoslav 
republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina, Bosnian Serb army sources said 
in a statement. 
  More than 100 artillery shells were fired on Bosnian Serb 
positions in the area. 
  The Serb side repulsed a Moslem infantry attack, in which it 
suffered no casualties, and the Moslems then continued to open 
artillery and machine-gun fire on Serb positions, the statement 
said. 
  The attack proves correct the increasingly frequent reports 
about concentration of Bosnian Moslem and Croat forces towards 
Serb positions in the valley of the river Sava, where they are 
planning to cut the only land corridor between the Serb Krajina 
regions in the west and the federal republic of Yugoslavia in 
the east. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

