<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Cooperation With Ukraine Discussed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Military Cooperation With Ukraine Discussed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1904160094 Bratislava PRAVDA in Slovak 15 Apr 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> AU1904160094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Next Time Specifically"] </F>
  [Text] Bratislava -- Provisions in the sphere of arms, 
supplies of materials and equipment, and services for the armed 
forces were the central issues discussed by delegations of the 
Slovak and Ukrainian Ministries of Defense in Bratislava 
yesterday. Possibilities of cooperation between military repair 
plants were also discussed. As regards technical provisions, 
the Slovak side expressed interest in, for example, purchasing 
spare parts for tanks, infantry combat vehicles, and radar 
systems. The Slovak Army also needs special fuel for missiles, 
lubricants for the air force, and other special supplies that 
used to be manufactured in the states of the former USSR. The 
two sides agreed to work out lists of offers that they will 
reassess under their own conditions. At their next meeting, 
they will discuss specific requirements and proposals on the 
basis of the two armies' potentials. 

</TEXT>

