<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs `Massing' for Attacks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs `Massing' for Attacks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2004110994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2004110994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mustafa Kurtovic] </F>
  [Excerpt] The situation in Gorazde is becoming ever more 
dramatic and the [Serbian] fascists are again massing along all 
the lines of attack on the town. The greatest concentration of 
chetniks and the largest amount of military hardware have been 
registered in the valley of the Praca River from the direction 
of Necici toward Jabucko Sedlo and Sjenokos. The situation in 
the town (?center) is taking on the bloodiest proportions. The 
innocent civilian population has been suffering from being out 
in the open. A wide-scale epidemic is threatening, so Gorazde 
is again sending an appeal for help for the suffering. The 
situation in the war hospital, the health center is worse than 
sad. No words can describe the situation there. Dozens of 
civilian victims killed by the criminals from the hills are 
lying in the streets of the town and on the bridges over the 
Drina. It was impossible to help them at all, as the chetniks 
blanketed every inch of the free Gorazde territory, and 
particularly the town center, with fierce artillery and sniper 
fire from the surrounding hills. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

