<H3> <TI>   TANJUG: Muslims Firing on Serbs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    TANJUG: Muslims Firing on Serbs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004083594 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0803 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004083594 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cajnice, 20 Apr (TANJUG) -- Following strong Muslim 
attacks yesterday, fighting on the Gorazde front resumed this 
morning with extreme ferocity along the entire line of 
confrontation, the Herzegovina corps command has announced. 
Muslims have so far failed to observe any of the existing 
cease- fire agreements, the Herzegovina corps command said, 
adding that Muslims will probably try to take advantage of the 
deployment of the UN Protection Force [UNPROFOR] in the area of 
Gorazde to provoke the Serbs and to accuse them of attacking the 
force of the international community. The most intense fire is 
coming from the center of the town. Muslims are using mortars, 
anti-aircraft weapons, and snipers, the Herzegovina corps 
command insists. 
  Despite orders from its high command, the Serbian side has 
been forced to respond to the Muslim attacks. The Herzegovina 
corps command insists that there is no truth in the Muslim 
claims that Serbian fighters have been pounding the Gorazde 
urban area with artillery weapons. Late yesterday afternoon, 
NATO planes overflew Serbian positions on the Gorazde front but 
at permitted altitude and did not engage in any combat activity. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

