<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Forty-three people, including 6 children, were 
killed and 112 were wounded in Gorazde yesterday, UNHCR 
spokesman Peter Kessler said on Wednesday [20 April]. A UNHCR 
building in Gorazde was hit twice at about 1800 yesterday 
evening, but there were no casualties among the staff, Kessler 
said, quoting reports by UNHCR personnel on the ground. The 
shelling of Gorazde continued on Wednesday morning, but less 
intensely, Ron Redman, UNHCR spokesman in Geneva, said after 
talking to Gorazde ham operators at 0700 this morning. 

</TEXT>

