<H4>    `Street Fighting' Reported </H4>

<F P=102> LD1904213794 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in English 2103 
GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1904213794 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chaos and street fighting are raging in Gorazde. 
That was reported this afternoon by local official Esad 
Obranovic, speaking for Radio Sarajevo via ham radio operators. 
Obranovic said the Gorazde hospital, some 200 meters from the 
scene of bitter conflicts on the right bank of the River Drina, 
was crammed with the wounded and people were still seeking 
shelter in its corridors. Meanwhile, house-to-house fighting 
was reported in the suburbs of Gorazde. The Bosnian prime 
minister Haris Silajdzic said the Serb forces had hit an ammonia 
storage facility and were continuing to open fire on the town. 

</TEXT>

