<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Attack Near Brcko Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Attack Near Brcko Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904192694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1823 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1904192694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Banja Luka, 19 Apr (TANJUG) -- Muslim and Croatian 
forces resumed attacks around 1600 today against the Serbian 
positions around Brcko, the information service of the republic 
of Srpska army's First Krajina Corps says in a statement issued 
in Banja Luka. The attack by the Muslim forces was launched 
this morning from the direction of Vranovaca hill, 8 kms south 
of Brcko, and the suburb of Boderiste, south of Brcko. 
  At the same time, Croatian Army forces, using the territory 
of the Republic of Croatia, together with the members of the 
Croatian Defense Council, fired 24 rockets from multiple rocket 
launchers and several artillery shells on the same Serbian 
positions. Two Serbian soldiers were seriously wounded in these 
attacks, and several residential buildings were damaged. 
  Today's attacks are a part of the intensified offensive 
activities by the Muslim and Croatian forces in Posavina and 
part of the big spring offensive by the so-called 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Army, which is frequently joined by Croatian 
Defense Council units. The attacks are aimed at cutting the 
road links between the two Serb krajinas and Semberija and 
Yugoslavia. 

</TEXT>

