  [Text] Belgrade, 19 Apr (TANJUG) -- The cabinet of Nikola 
Koljevic, vice president of the republic of Sprska, today 
informed the aid organization Medecins Sans Frontieres (MSF) 
that the republic of Srpska authorities have authorized this 
organization, too, to carry on with its humanitarian convoy 
operations. It was announced yesterday that, under an agreement 
between the Serbian authorities and Yasushi Akashi, the UN 
secretary general's special envoy, the UNHCR, the International 
Committee of the Red Cross, and Handicap International can 
resume their humanitarian convoy operations. In the TANJUG 
report, Medecin Sans Frontieres was left out by mistake. 

