<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Accuses STV of Lack of Objectivity </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Accuses STV of Lack of Objectivity </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1904125594 Bratislava PRAVDA in Slovak 14 Apr 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> AU1904125594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Slovak Television Perceived as Unobjective"] </F>
  [Text] Bratislava--The Press and Information Department 
(TIO) of the Slovak Government Office regards the coverage of 
the parliamentary debate on the Slovak Government Policy 
Statement in the first issue of STV's [Slovak Television] 
"Aktuality" program on 12 April as incompatible with the STV's 
legal status as a public corporation. This is stated in a 
statement by the TIO of the Slovak Government Office that was 
made available to TA SR yesterday. The statement draws 
attention to the fact that the TIO of the Slovak Government 
Office considers the failure to make public a single idea from 
Slovak Prime Minister Jozef Moravcik's speech, while at the same 
time including a statement by Movement for a Democratic Slovakia 
[HZDS] Deputy Olga Keltosova, a violation of the objectivity of 
information. The STV is legally obliged to maintain 
objectivity, the statement says. 

</TEXT>

