<H3> <TI>   Government Replaces TA SR Director </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Replaces TA SR Director </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904172094 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1500 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1904172094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1500 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Slovak Government today discussed the statement 
of some heads of district offices and former government 
plenipotentiaries in which they accuse the president of grossly 
offending parliamentary democracy. After thoroughly reassessing 
the overall situation in the state administration, in particular 
in order to ensure the implementation of tasks arising from the 
law on the reorganization of local administration, the 
government decided to recall 26 heads of district offices. 
  In addition, the government recalled Dusan Kleiman from the 
post of director general of the News Agency of the Slovak 
Republic [TA SR] and appointed Ivan Melichercik as the new 
director. At the same time, it agreed with the proposal to 
solve the economic problems of Slovak Radio and approved the 
request for radio broadcasts in line with the law on the state 
budget. The government authorized the Ministry of Culture to 
make this request specific so that the Ministry of Finance may 
provide the financing for this request. 

</TEXT>

