<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkish Envoy Summoned Over Attack on Car </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904184894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1719 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1904184894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Belgrade, 19 Apr (TANJUG) -- The Turkish charge 
d'affaires has been handed a note of sharpest protest by the 
Yugoslav Government over the terrorist attack in Ankara early 
this morning, in which a car of our embassy's first secretary, 
which had been parked in front of his house, was blown up and 
destroyed. The protest note expresses indignation over the 
terrorist act, which threatened the life and property of the 
Yugoslav diplomat and members of his family. It is stressed 
that the Yugoslav Government considers the Turkish authorities 
fully responsible for the terrorist act, because -- despite the 
Yugoslav side's warnings about threats and hostile 
demonstrations against the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia -- 
they have not adopted efficient measures to protect the Yugoslav 
diplomatic and consular missions, their personnel, and members 
of their families. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

