BFN 

  [Text] The Czech Republic wants the European Bank for 
Reconstruction and Development [EBRD] to help, in particular in 
restructuring Czech industry. This was mentioned in today's 
speech delivered by Czech Finance Minister Ivan Kocarnik at the 
EBRD conference in St. Petersburg. 
  According to the minister, the Czech Republic has already 
concluded the first stage of the transition to a market economy. 
However, the country's economy is now confronted with great 
posttransformation challenges. The minister also expressed his 
appreciation of the positive changes that have occurred in the 
EBRD since Jacques de Larossiere became its director. 

