<H3> <TI>   RDP Group Arms Consortium Adds 4 Enterprises </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    RDP Group Arms Consortium Adds 4 Enterprises </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2004092894 Prague HOSPODARSKE NOVINY in Czech 15 Apr 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU2004092894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague HOSPODARSKE NOVINY </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "(joe)": "The RDP Group Arms Consortium Is </F>
Expanding"] 
  [Text] Jihlava--The RDP Group shareholding company, which 
affiliates the largest special production manufacturers, will 
expand to include at least another four enterprises; 
negotiations are under way on the entry of several more 
enterprises. This was one of the conclusions reached yesterday 
at the company's general assembly. The RDP Group's aim is to 
create a system of mutual cooperation involving the Czech Army, 
the central bodies of state administration, and the arms 
manufacturers and to participate in the modernization of the 
Czech Army. According to officials from the Defense Ministry, 
the suppliers of final equipment for the Czech Army should, on 
principle, be domestic entities. Roughly 30 percent of the 2.5 
percent of the state budget earmarked for the Defense Ministry 
has been set aside for modernizing the Czech Army. The ministry 
is now drawing up the priorities of the program for the Army's 
modernization. The modernized T-72 tank and the Aero L-59 
aircraft, for example, with all probability will be among the 
new military systems. 

</TEXT>

