<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Granic, Silajdzic Coordinate Efforts on Gorazde </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Granic, Silajdzic Coordinate Efforts on Gorazde </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904174694 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1700 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1904174694 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mate Granic, Croatian deputy prime minister and 
minister of foreign affairs, had a phone conversation with 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Prime Minister Haris Silajdzic today. 
  Granic and Silajdzic discussed the situation in Gorazde and 
the coordination of the activities of the two states in the 
international arena -- particularly in the United Nations and 
the EU -- and in political and humanitarian fields. They 
expressed pleasure with the results achieved so far in the 
implementation of the Washington agreement and agreed that both 
sides should persist with it so that the international community 
might halt the Serb aggression against Gorazde and so that 
conditions be created for the continuation of the initiated 
peace process. 
  Minister Granic informed Prime Minister Silajdzic that 
Slobodan Lang, Croatian ambassador at the Croatian Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs in charge of humanitarian affairs, is in 
Sarajevo to coordinate humanitarian activities. They also 
discussed preparations for the announced visit by Croatian 
President Franjo Tudjman to Sarajevo and agreed that the visit 
should go ahead as soon as security conditions allow. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

