<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   NATO Needs `Political Will' for Air Strikes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NATO Needs `Political Will' for Air Strikes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1904094894 Paris AFP in English 0922 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1904094894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brussels, April 19 (AFP) -- NATO will make no 
decision on air strikes to protect UN safe areas in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina until the governments of member states show a 
"political will" to act military, NATO officials said Tuesday 
[19 April]. 
  NATO military commanders must also closely study the 
situation in the UN-declared safe zones under Bosnian Serb siege 
before replying to UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali, who 
asked NATO Monday [18 April] for airstrike authorisation. 
  Bosnian Serbs are on the point of taking the Moslem town of 
Gorazde, one of the six so-called safe areas. 

</TEXT>

