<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cease-Fire Agreement Reached in Gorazde </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cease-Fire Agreement Reached in Gorazde </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004003894 Belgrade TANJUG in English 0020 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2004003894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, April 19 (TANJUG) - Representatives of the 
Bosnian Serb Republic and the United Nations Protection Force 
(UNPROFOR) reached a temporary agreement on Gorazde in Pale late 
on Tuesday [19 April] evening, the Bosnian Serb news agency SRNA 
reported. "The memorandum on temporary arrangements for 
Gorazde" calls for an end to combat actions around the town and 
the deployment of two UNPROFOR platoons with around 100 men. 
"Serbs agree that they immediately cease all combat activities 
in an area 3 km from central Gorazde on the left bank of the 
Drina, unless they are attacked," said the memorandum which was 
signed by Bosnian Serb Assembly President Momcilo Krajisnik and 
UNPROFOR Civil administration Head Victor Andreyev. 

</TEXT>

