<H3> <TI>   Diplomatic Ties Established With Ukraine </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Diplomatic Ties Established With Ukraine </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904204394 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1853 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1904204394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, April 19 (TANJUG) -- Yugoslavia 
(Serbia/Montenegro) and Ukraine have established diplomatic 
relations, which has been made official by the foreign 
ministries exchanging notes, the Yugoslav ministry said on 
Tuesday [19 April]. In line with this, Yugoslavia has already 
opened its embassy in Kiev. The establishment of diplomatic 
ties continues long years of all-round cooperation and 
friendship between the two nations and affirms their commitment 
to deepening and consolidation friendly relations and extensive 
cooperation, the ministry said. 

</TEXT>

