<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Bulgaria </F>
<H3> <TI>   BSP's Videnov on UN Convoy Decision </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    BSP's Videnov on UN Convoy Decision </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1904170394 Sofia BTA in English 1530 GMT 19 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1904170394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Threat for Macedonia Is Myth, Bulgarian Socialists Say" -- </F>
BTA headline] 
  [Text] Sofia, April 19 (BTA) -- It was a wrong decision 
that turned positive, former Communists' Bulgarian Socialist 
Party (BSP) leader Zhan Videnov said at a news conference, 
commenting on parliament's decision as to the transit of 
Macedonia-bound UN equipment via Bulgaria. According to Mr. 
Videnov, the positive thing about the decision was that it 
clearly stated it set no precedent and should not be repeated. 
  BSP deputy floor leader Nikolay Kamov voiced his concern 
over 
statements made by representatives of the Union of the 
Democratic Forces (SDS) which, according to Mr. Kamov, did not 
rule out the possibility for once again taking this decision. 
"The SDS refuse to firmly state that they are against the 
passage of foreign military troops via Bulgaria's territory," 
Mr. Videnov also said. According to him, it is dangerous for 
this country to think that a series of single acts leave its 
stand unchanged. If approached again with this request, we are 
most likely to again say "yes," the BSP leader said. 
  According to Mr. Videnov, the great powers now see the 
conflict in former Yugoslavia as a global, religious-based one. 
The processes in the Balkans cannot be a concern for the great 
powers only. Serbia-Montenegro is not hostile to Macedonia 
[Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] and this (that 
Macedonia's security is jeopardized) is a myth certain political 
forces in Bulgaria have created to justify their actions, 
according to the BSP leader. 
  The Socialists have not yet taken an official stand on the 
decision of the Russian Duma to demand lifting of the 
Yugo-embargo, Klara Marinova of the BSP told the news conference. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-9004 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu076__a94022" </HT>


<HEADER>
