<H3> <TI>   UN Convoy `Robbed' Prior to Arrival </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Convoy `Robbed' Prior to Arrival </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1904111894 Sofia BTA in English 1040 GMT 19 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1904111894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From BTA's 19 April "Press Review"] </F>
  [Excerpt] Sofia, April 19 (BTA) -- All newspapers report 
that the trainload of UN military equipment bound for Macedonia 
[The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM], crossed 
Bulgaria through Ruse and Sofia and is now in Kyustendil where 
the convoy is expecting an Austrian company to unload it and 
transfer it to Macedonia. The dailies report that the convoy 
had been robbed before it arrived in Bulgaria and publish photos 
of the train with the military equipment. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

